    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.56,
      "end": 5.32,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.32,
      "end": 10.72,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.88,
      "end": 14.58,
      "text": "Aesop's fables, the dog and the shadow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.9,
      "end": 20.46,
      "text": "A dog was crossing a plank bridge over a stream with a piece of meat in his mouth,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 20.96,
      "end": 23.12,
      "text": "when he happened to see his own reflection in the water.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.88,
      "end": 27.12,
      "text": "He thought it was another dog with a piece of meat twice as big,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.62,
      "end": 32.02,
      "text": "so he let go his own and flew at the other dog to get the larger piece.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 33.18,
      "end": 36.12,
      "text": "But of course, all that happened was that he got neither.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 37.14,
      "end": 41.08,
      "text": "For one was only a shadow and the other was carried away by the current.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 42.54,
      "end": 44.74,
      "text": "End of the dog and the shadow.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
